# XXE Prevention

Source: cursor-security-rules. Applies to all code that parses or processes XML.

## 1. Disable DTDs and External Entities
- XML parsers must have DTDs disabled and must not resolve external entities.
- Use safe libraries (e.g. defusedxml in Python, secure processing features in Java).

## 2. Use Secure Parser Features / Libraries
- Choose parsers with XXE protection by default; verify that external DTDs and entities are disallowed.

## 3. Restrict Schema and XInclude
- Do not allow remote or file-based schema/XInclude/XSLT on untrusted XML unless sandboxed.

## 4. Limit Resource Consumption
- Configure limits (size, entity expansion depth, timeouts) to prevent Billion Laughs / DoS.

## 5. Validate Input
- Validate XML against a known schema or allow-list; reject malformed or unexpected content.

## 6. Do Not Log Sensitive XML
- Do not log raw XML that may contain credentials or PII.
